  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Living Conditions and Populations Affected by Drought and Conflict in Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the high level of displacement and the increased humanitarian needs, IOM will provide coordinated life-saving humanitarian response to crisis-affected populations through the provision of shelter and non-food items (S-NFI). Furthermore, through its role as Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM) Cluster co-lead, IOM will address the needs of Internally Displaced Populations (IDPs) in Somalia by responding to new and protracted displacement, improving and upgrading basic services in sites, and supporting the overall drought response. In particular, IOM will support displaced populations and vulnerable communities through S-NFI interventions by assessing needs, coordinating with local authorities and humanitarian partners; and, procuring, transporting and distributing emergency shelter kits and NFI to identified households in need of coverage and/or reinforcement.</narrative>
  </description>
